<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-19T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1134: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-19T12:00:00-04:00">June
                                        19, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>138. Referring to my 136, June 18, 11 p.m. paragraph headed <hi rend="italic">Aviation</hi>, first sentence which now reads “All
                                military aviation except observation planes at sea to be abolished”
                                should be changed to read “All military aviation except for
                                intelligence and scouting purposes to be abolished”. This is a
                                variation from instructions previously sent you but is made because
                                the President feels that sentiment of the country demands the
                                retention of military aviation for these purposes even on land.
                                Please note correction.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>